Bootstrap behavior (`post-create.sh`)

When container is created, it does all of this:

- Enables `corepack`
- Installs global package managers `pnpm` and `yarn`
- Upgrades Python packaging tools and installs `uv`
- Seeds env files when available:
	`.env.sample -> .env` and `.env.example -> .env.local`
- Installs JS dependencies by lockfile priority:
	`pnpm-lock.yaml` -> `yarn.lock` -> `package-lock.json`/`npm-shrinkwrap.json` -> fallback `npm install`
- Installs Python dependencies from:
	`requirements-dev.txt`, `requirements.txt`, `pyproject.toml`, and `src/backend/pyproject.toml` when present

Attach guidance (`post-attach.sh`)

Every attach prints:

- service endpoints summary
- quick health/test commands
- common start commands
- one-line command to enable optional Ollama lane

It also now enforces a writable runtime directory for socket-based extension locks:

- creates `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR` (default `/tmp/vscode-runtime`)
- applies `chmod 700`
- reduces .NET runtime installer lock conflicts in container sessions

